subject: p13484161
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest were obtained. There is prominence of the interstitial markings suggesting moderate interstitial edema. No large pleural effusion is seen. There is no evidence of pneumothorax. The cardiac silhouette is enlarged. The aorta is tortuous.
Impression: Enlarged cardiac silhouette and moderate interstitial edema.
